# {{display}}

Scaffolded by `nmp init {{name}}`.

## Layout

| Path | What |
|------|------|
| `nmp.toml` | App manifest. Declares the NMP dependency policy, kernel, protocol modules, and app modules. Consumed by `nmp gen modules`. |
| `crates/{{pkg}}/` | Your app's core. Owns the app's nouns (`EntryRecord`, …). One Domain / View / Action module. **App nouns never go in `nmp-core`** (doctrine D0). |
| `crates/{{pkg}}/examples/shell.rs` | Minimal headless shell stub. |

## Build the skeleton

```sh
cargo check                              # the {{pkg}} skeleton compiles as-is
cargo test -p {{pkg}}                    # skeleton tests pass
cargo run --example shell -p {{pkg}}     # headless shell stub
```

## Generate the FFI crate

```sh
nmp gen modules            # emits apps/{{name}}/nmp-app-{{name}}
nmp gen modules --check    # verifies it is up to date (deterministic)
```

`nmp gen modules` produces the per-app FFI crate `nmp-app-{{name}}`
(`AppAction` / `AppUpdate` / `ViewSpec` enums, the `FfiApp` wrapper). The
generated crate follows the `[nmp]` dependency policy in `nmp.toml`: versioned
release-consumer apps use published `nmp-*` crates, while framework-development
apps use a local checkout path.

## Upgrade NMP

```sh
nmp upgrade --to 0.2.0
nmp gen modules
nmp gen modules --check
nmp doctor
```

## Next steps

1. Replace `Entry` in `crates/{{pkg}}/src/lib.rs` with your real domain.
2. Add protocol modules to `nmp.toml` (`protocol = ["nmp-nip01", …]`).
3. Re-run `nmp gen modules`.
